  "title": "Amazon Q1 2026 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2026-04-30T21:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2026_Q1",
  "location": "Seattle, WA",
  "url": "https://ir.aboutamazon.com/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "andy-jassy",
      "speaker_name": "Andy Jassy",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "AWS grew 22% in Q1 2026 to $38.7 billion, ahead of expectations. The AI tailwind is not slowing. We are seeing demand across every vertical — financial services, healthcare, manufacturing, public sector. Amazon Nova, our proprietary foundation model family, is now used by over 20,000 enterprise customers on Bedrock. We expect to invest over $110 billion in infrastructure in 2026. Amazon Healthcare AI is progressing toward a launch of AI-powered clinical documentation tools in 500 hospitals by year-end."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "brian-olsavsky",
      "speaker_name": "Brian Olsavsky",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:20:00",
      "text": "Q1 2026 net sales were $192.4 billion, up 10% year-over-year. AWS operating income was $15.3 billion, with a margin of 39.5%. Advertising revenue grew 18% to $16.2 billion. Total capex in Q1 was $28.6 billion, consistent with our full-year commitment. We are guiding Q2 net sales to $195–200 billion and AWS revenue growth above 20%."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:38:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Mark Mahaney at Evercore ISI."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-mark-mahaney",
      "speaker_name": "Mark Mahaney",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:38:20",
      "text": "Andy, Nova model adoption at 20,000 enterprise customers is significant. How do you think about the competitive moat versus Anthropic's Claude and OpenAI on Bedrock?"
    }
  ],
